Y’all, today has been an all you can eat buffet of emotions. My beautiful ass show, that my amazing team of writers & I worked so hard on premiered today. @sagaftra announced that we’re striking today as well. It’s wild & sad that it’s even come to this because what we’re all asking for is not unreasonable. 

Writing a show together is a funky
special bond. You spend more time with these people than your family, you share some of your most personal, embarrassing, painful & hilarious times in your life, and it’s all for the love & art of storytelling. It’s community. 

I love my show. I love my writers. I love my actors. 

See y’all on the picket line with meh crocks on cause a bish is about comfort. 

Thank you @danisanwitz @gracyact @ianedwardscomic @solomongeorgio @genderless_gap_ad @hillhands @julialindon 

Y’all are the real MVPs 🤘🏽

Honey! Last week, we had the honor of setting the table for author, actress, comedian, and executive producer @michellebuteau during the Portland stop of her tour!

Spoiler: SHE IS EVERYTHING!

We laughed, cried, shared, and affirmed one another. Women from a variety of industries shared their stories and engaged in discussions about their journey as Black and Brown women in their careers and lives. Our gathering was intimate, but the lessons and love will continue to expand beyond.  Thank you, Michelle, for sharing your heart, wisdom, and time with us! You’re the epitome of the power of representation. Thank you for writing, producing, and sharing OUR stories. We are rooting for you!

Here to Stay has been on a journey of evolution, but the heartbeat has remained the same.

We're building opportunities to champion women at various levels of their personal and professional journeys. Click the link in our bio to stay informed on our upcoming experiences!

A heartfelt thank you to all the wonderful humans and businesses that we worked with to make this night happen:

Anne & the rest of Michelle’s team!
